4
00:01:14.940 --> 00:01:16.780
I looked up to your father.

5
00:01:19.900 --> 00:01:24.540
He and my big brother
were like two heroes to me.

6
00:01:30.940 --> 00:01:34.020
Your grandfather
should end up as they did.

7
00:01:37.900 --> 00:01:40.820
When my nephew told me
what you were doing.

8
00:01:41.840 --> 00:01:43.320
I was afraid for you.

9
00:01:53.880 --> 00:01:55.440
But now.

10
00:01:57.480 --> 00:01:59.320
the war has started.

11
00:02:01.960 --> 00:02:03.280
We have to finish it.

12
00:02:17.200 --> 00:02:18.400
I'm nearly done.

13
00:02:41.760 --> 00:02:43.080
Give me your arm.

14
00:02:52.840 --> 00:02:55.320
Change the bandage twice a day.

15
00:02:56.720 --> 00:02:58.040
And rest.

16
00:03:01.000 --> 00:03:04.120
Take these after every meal
or it'll get infected.

17
00:03:05.800 --> 00:03:07.200
Thank you.

18
00:03:12.720 --> 00:03:17.080
There's a lot of people
counting on you.

19
00:03:19.400 --> 00:03:21.480
I hope you know what you're doing.

20
00:03:23.360 --> 00:03:24.480
I do.

21
00:03:25.360 --> 00:03:26.840
I'm going to see Italo.

22
00:03:47.000 --> 00:03:48.480
Hello?

23
00:03:50.080 --> 00:03:51.840
Baby. where are you?

24
00:03:52.040 --> 00:03:55.240
Listen. things went wrong.
You gotta run.

25
00:03:55.520 --> 00:03:58.480
Take Mico and find my grandfather.
Do what he says.

26
00:03:58.800 --> 00:04:00.320
Your grandfather?

27
00:04:01.920 --> 00:04:03.520
Stefano. what happened?

28
00:04:08.680 --> 00:04:10.320
How did it go?

29
00:04:12.040 --> 00:04:13.680
Good.

30
00:04:17.760 --> 00:04:19.520
How did he say he got shot?

31
00:04:23.340 --> 00:04:25.700
He didn't tell me. why?

32
00:04:28.960 --> 00:04:30.960
Because they didn't shoot him.

33
00:04:34.040 --> 00:04:35.560
He shot himself.

34
00:06:47.000 --> 00:06:51.040
SAHARA DESSERT. MALI

35
00:07:16.640 --> 00:07:18.720
It started four months ago.

36
00:07:21.000 --> 00:07:23.360
I was in the shower
at the athletic club.

37
00:07:25.880 --> 00:07:27.560
I dropped a shampoo bottle.

38
00:07:31.800 --> 00:07:34.160
And I told myself it was nothing.

39
00:07:37.840 --> 00:07:39.280
It happened a few more times

40
00:07:39.360 --> 00:07:43.000
so I went to the doctor
and she gave me some pills and stuff.

41
00:07:52.440 --> 00:07:54.000
Why didn't you tell us?

42
00:07:55.800 --> 00:07:58.000
I didn't want anything to change.

43
00:08:40.000 --> 00:08:41.440
What's going on?

44
00:08:43.080 --> 00:08:45.920
Jihadists. They'll escort us.

45
00:08:47.360 --> 00:08:49.720
- What do you mean?
- This is their route.

46
00:08:50.320 --> 00:08:51.960
They control this area.

47
00:08:53.560 --> 00:08:55.560
This is how they make money.

48
00:09:07.240 --> 00:09:08.880
Do you know that guy?

49
00:09:13.640 --> 00:09:14.840
Not him.

50
00:09:20.400 --> 00:09:22.280
You better cover your hair.

51
00:09:23.320 --> 00:09:25.320
Okay.

52
00:09:41.240 --> 00:09:45.960
Peace. My name's Omar.
I'm a friend of Mohamed Hamaha.

53
00:09:48.480 --> 00:09:51.440
Mohamed was killed
by the French yesterday.

54
00:09:53.120 --> 00:09:56.560
- Who are they?
- Americans.

55
00:09:58.320 --> 00:10:00.360
I'm sorry about Mohamed.

56
00:10:01.440 --> 00:10:03.320
I don't like Americans.

57
00:10:07.280 --> 00:10:10.640
- Can you read his lips?
- No. not in French.

58
00:10:27.520 --> 00:10:30.760
What's going on?
What happened? What did he say?

59
00:10:32.120 --> 00:10:34.040
He wants a hundred kilos.

60
00:10:35.680 --> 00:10:37.640
We're not in a position to bargain.

61
00:10:37.720 --> 00:10:40.280
We gotta get
this cargo to Casablanca.

62
00:10:47.960 --> 00:10:49.520
Omar!

63
00:11:34.520 --> 00:11:36.880
- Bring them a blanket.
- Okay.

64
00:11:54.520 --> 00:11:55.960
For the cold.

65
00:12:02.280 --> 00:12:03.640
Thanks.

66
00:12:21.560 --> 00:12:23.200
Look what I got.

67
00:12:24.320 --> 00:12:27.640
- Where'd you get this?
- They gave them to me.

68
00:12:44.960 --> 00:12:48.760
I would never have asked you
to go with this shipment if I'd known.

69
00:12:53.840 --> 00:12:57.080
What the fuck. Chris!
Where do you think this ends?

70
00:12:57.440 --> 00:13:00.240
I don't need
a fucking lecture on Huntington's.

71
00:13:07.600 --> 00:13:10.160
You told me Dad wanted me involved.

72
00:13:15.600 --> 00:13:17.440
I want to see this through.

73
00:14:03.720 --> 00:14:06.440
- What's happening?
- They're buying weapons.

74
00:14:07.120 --> 00:14:09.280
There's a lot of uranium in this region.

75
00:14:09.360 --> 00:14:13.200
The French want it and the Malian
government is selling these people out.

76
00:14:13.280 --> 00:14:15.440
They are fighting for their land.

77
00:14:17.120 --> 00:14:20.560
The Tuaregs have always been here
but no one cares about that.

78
00:15:16.200 --> 00:15:19.240
- What is this place?
- Jihadists stronghold.

79
00:15:21.080 --> 00:15:24.280
They're occupying the city.
It's under the sharia law.

80
00:16:27.240 --> 00:16:28.840
Peace be with you.

81
00:16:29.400 --> 00:16:31.280
- How's it going?
- Well and you?

82
00:16:31.600 --> 00:16:33.040
Well.

83
00:16:37.120 --> 00:16:40.040
- Are we staying here?
- I don't know.

84
00:16:49.800 --> 00:16:51.120
Let's go.

85
00:16:54.800 --> 00:16:55.960
Peace.

86
00:16:57.680 --> 00:17:00.840
- Get out.
- What's he saying?

87
00:17:02.240 --> 00:17:03.880
Easy.

88
00:17:04.520 --> 00:17:05.880
Easy.

89
00:17:08.600 --> 00:17:10.240
Okay. just go.

90
00:17:10.440 --> 00:17:11.880
Emma. no! Wait!

91
00:17:13.520 --> 00:17:17.880
- Tell her to go back in the car!
- Emma. please. Back to the car. please.

92
00:17:18.080 --> 00:17:19.640
That's my sister.

93
00:17:20.640 --> 00:17:22.360
- Stay in the car!
- Easy.

94
00:17:22.720 --> 00:17:24.040
Emma. please.

95
00:17:28.880 --> 00:17:31.680
- Where are they going to take him?
- I don't know.

96
00:17:35.800 --> 00:17:38.640
Just do what they say.
It's going to be fine.

97
00:17:45.080 --> 00:17:47.640
What is he saying to me?
What's he saying?

98
00:17:51.200 --> 00:17:53.520
Okay. you can go with them.
You can go.

99
00:17:54.280 --> 00:17:55.680
Easy. easy.

100
00:17:57.120 --> 00:17:58.720
You stay in the car.

101
00:17:59.480 --> 00:18:01.880
Stay in the car! Stay there!

102
00:18:36.600 --> 00:18:38.760
Come here!

103
00:21:02.360 --> 00:21:05.520
Where's my brother?
Do you speak French?

104
00:21:08.520 --> 00:21:11.480
Do you speak English?
My brother.

105
00:21:13.840 --> 00:21:15.600
My brother.

106
00:21:16.720 --> 00:21:20.600
They've taken him somewhere. Can you
tell me where they've taken him?

107
00:21:21.080 --> 00:21:23.560
Can you help me?
Could I come out?

108
00:21:54.960 --> 00:21:58.920
Breaking news: there's been another
terrorist attack in Ouagadougo.

109
00:21:59.000 --> 00:22:03.680
where a handful of extremists
are holding dozens of people hostage

110
00:22:03.760 --> 00:22:06.520
in a hotel in the heart of the city.

111
00:22:07.480 --> 00:22:10.520
Gunfire was heard close to the hotel

112
00:22:10.880 --> 00:22:15.240
but there is no information
regarding casualties.

113
00:22:15.880 --> 00:22:18.040
Authorities have not received
any demands

114
00:22:18.120 --> 00:22:20.120
for the release of the hostages.

115
00:22:20.960 --> 00:22:24.440
One of the attackers
has been identified as Tamil Yiarango.

116
00:22:24.520 --> 00:22:26.240
son of militant Brahim Yiarango.

117
00:22:26.640 --> 00:22:28.920
We have not yet established

118
00:22:29.120 --> 00:22:32.480
whether Yiarango senior
is one of the attackers.

119
00:22:32.560 --> 00:22:36.240
Over to Bernard Erting
at the scene of the attack.

120
00:22:37.360 --> 00:22:39.800
The attack was carried out
by four armed men

121
00:22:40.000 --> 00:22:42.640
who opened fire
on a crowded French restaurant.

122
00:22:42.720 --> 00:22:45.800
The patrons
were brought into the hotel...

123
00:23:31.000 --> 00:23:32.960
There's been an attack!

124
00:23:33.560 --> 00:23:35.840
French Special Forces.

125
00:23:41.560 --> 00:23:45.320
They're all dead.
Everyone is dead.

126
00:23:58.280 --> 00:23:59.600
Emma!

127
00:24:00.640 --> 00:24:01.920
We got to move.

128
00:24:04.120 --> 00:24:06.760
There was an attack.
French drone.

129
00:24:08.600 --> 00:24:11.600
- Chris was with them.
- I can't leave without Chris.

130
00:24:12.360 --> 00:24:15.640
They're all dead. All of them.
We have to leave.

131
00:24:17.480 --> 00:24:19.880
- Now.
- I can't leave without Chris!

132
00:24:20.080 --> 00:24:24.280
Emma. your brother is dead.
Brahim took Chris with him yesterday.

133
00:24:24.360 --> 00:24:26.560
I can't leave without Chris!

134
00:24:26.640 --> 00:24:28.440
- He's dead.
- No!

135
00:24:28.520 --> 00:24:32.960
He's not coming back. Please.
listen to me. He's not coming back.

136
00:24:35.520 --> 00:24:39.480
Stay with me.
Grab this. grab it. Go.

137
00:24:40.280 --> 00:24:43.360
And you stay behind me at all times.
C'mon. trust me.

138
00:24:46.920 --> 00:24:48.400
Stay close to me.

139
00:25:30.520 --> 00:25:31.960
Go.

140
00:25:34.200 --> 00:25:35.560
Careful. Check.

141
00:25:49.560 --> 00:25:52.920
No men on the left.
Go. go!

142
00:26:04.440 --> 00:26:05.880
Wait.

143
00:26:10.360 --> 00:26:11.800
Go check.

144
00:26:13.680 --> 00:26:15.520
About six men.

145
00:26:18.680 --> 00:26:20.080
Okay. go.

146
00:26:31.000 --> 00:26:32.240
Go. go!

147
00:26:57.360 --> 00:26:58.600
Now!

148
00:27:05.520 --> 00:27:06.840
Now!

149
00:27:38.720 --> 00:27:40.080
Press hard.

150
00:27:43.960 --> 00:27:46.560
Press hard. Like this.

151
00:28:11.920 --> 00:28:13.200
Brahim!

152
00:28:49.000 --> 00:28:51.520
- Are we staying here?
- I don't know.

153
00:29:08.040 --> 00:29:10.240
- What's he saying?
- Easy!

154
00:29:11.640 --> 00:29:14.680
Just go.
Emma. no!

155
00:29:15.880 --> 00:29:17.400
That's my sister.

156
00:29:59.560 --> 00:30:01.240
Wear this tonight.

157
00:30:06.440 --> 00:30:09.080
I wore it in when I married your mother.

158
00:30:29.160 --> 00:30:31.440
You are my favorite son.

159
00:30:35.000 --> 00:30:36.880
Say goodbye to mother for me.

160
00:31:32.280 --> 00:31:33.800
That was your son.

161
00:31:35.600 --> 00:31:38.400
That was your son back there.
wasn't it?

162
00:31:43.520 --> 00:31:45.120
You have...

163
00:31:45.720 --> 00:31:47.680
The same eyes.

164
00:31:59.840 --> 00:32:01.120
You don't know us.

165
00:32:04.360 --> 00:32:06.160
You will never know us.

166
00:32:14.520 --> 00:32:17.080
Whatever he's doing.
I hope it's worth it.

167
00:32:49.680 --> 00:32:50.880
What is that?

168
00:32:53.000 --> 00:32:54.880
- You are a doctor.
- What?

169
00:32:55.440 --> 00:32:57.080
Only doctors have access.

170
00:32:59.200 --> 00:33:00.640
I need to go inside.

171
00:33:01.400 --> 00:33:05.880
You are a doctor. Act well
and you will see your sister again.

172
00:33:08.240 --> 00:33:11.000
I have to bless my newborn son.

173
00:33:55.440 --> 00:33:58.920
He's an American doctor
with World Peace Doctors.

174
00:33:59.520 --> 00:34:01.520
He has to examine some patients.

175
00:34:05.360 --> 00:34:07.720
- Good evening.
- Your access permit.

176
00:34:20.080 --> 00:34:22.600
Are you Dr. Christopher Lynwood?

177
00:34:22.800 --> 00:34:25.360
Yes. I'm a doctor.
I have patients inside.

178
00:34:25.560 --> 00:34:28.240
- And these men are with you?
- Yes.

179
00:35:33.720 --> 00:35:34.840
Wait.

180
00:35:40.600 --> 00:35:41.840
You've come.

181
00:35:46.520 --> 00:35:47.760
Who is he?

182
00:35:51.760 --> 00:35:53.320
Let me see my new baby.

183
00:35:56.680 --> 00:35:58.080
Where's Tamil?

184
00:36:05.440 --> 00:36:07.400
He's on his way to God.

185
00:36:18.880 --> 00:36:20.480
God is great.

186
00:36:22.560 --> 00:36:24.640
There is no other God but Allah.

187
00:36:37.600 --> 00:36:38.840
Water.

188
00:37:08.840 --> 00:37:10.080
Here.

189
00:38:08.960 --> 00:38:10.120
I can't have kids.

190
00:38:13.640 --> 00:38:18.960
I mean...
I could. but it would be cruel.

191
00:38:19.680 --> 00:38:22.440
I have a disease
that I got from my mom

192
00:38:26.160 --> 00:38:30.120
and my kid would have 50-50 chance
of having the same disease that we had.

193
00:38:30.320 --> 00:38:32.960
And even if the coin
flips in their favor.

194
00:38:35.240 --> 00:38:37.280
he'd still have to watch me suffer.

195
00:38:43.560 --> 00:38:45.360
Watch me die.

196
00:38:50.200 --> 00:38:52.440
I think my parents had me tested
before I was born

197
00:38:52.640 --> 00:38:57.160
because I could always tell that they
knew from the way they treated me.

198
00:39:00.400 --> 00:39:02.280
The way they looked at me.

199
00:39:08.680 --> 00:39:11.200
Same way you looked
at your elder son today.

200
00:41:59.000 --> 00:42:00.560
Come on!

201
00:42:09.200 --> 00:42:10.560
Come on...

202
00:42:14.120 --> 00:42:15.400
Come on!

203
00:44:46.920 --> 00:44:49.240
Let's go!

204
00:44:50.280 --> 00:44:53.120
- What's he doing here?
- He was with them.

205
00:44:55.280 --> 00:44:57.320
Brahim! In the car!

206
00:44:58.560 --> 00:45:02.960
Hurry! Quick!
Don't let Brahim die!

207
00:45:10.600 --> 00:45:12.480
Get him inside.

208
00:45:14.000 --> 00:45:16.400
You. beat it!

209
00:45:18.440 --> 00:45:20.680
Beat it! Go on. beat it!

210
00:45:25.560 --> 00:45:28.880
Can you get in the car?
Drive the car.

211
00:45:39.240 --> 00:45:40.640
The trucks!

212
00:46:16.880 --> 00:46:18.440
Okay. I've got you.

213
